                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13079358" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 4 Aug 2011 12:33:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm...I actually noticed this a week or two ago, but thought it was likely an existing issue from back when Solr tried to handle more of this type of tracking/buffering. I forgot about it before making an issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But you are right - previously this was reset in the close writer method...but we no longer close the writer on commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13079378" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 4 Aug 2011 13:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Separately, we might track the number of docs pending for soft commit...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13102089" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sat, 10 Sep 2011 17:26:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this was fixed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
